    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-19T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="912"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/6938</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-19T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1773. Your 3075, April 13, 5 p.m. Department not prepared to have Legation
                    associate itself with the Allied legations in note to Swiss Government without
                    facts as to incidents making note desirable. See stipulations of article 7,
                    treaty of 1850 with Switzerland.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
